thms (avoid O(n²))\n- [ ] Pagination for large datasets\n- [ ] Caching implemented for hot data\n- [ ] Async operations for I/O\n- [ ] Worker threads for CPU-intensive tasks\n- [ ] Database indexes on frequently queried columns\n- [ ] Memory profiling done\n- [ ] Load testing completed`,\n    tags: [\"performance\", \"optimization\", \"n-plus-1\", \"caching\", \"profiling\"],\n    confidence: 1\n  },\n  {\n    name: \"Boundary Condition Fixes\",\n    summary: \"Handle edge cases including array bounds, integer overflow, null checks, and input validation for robust code.\",\n    content: `# Boundary Condition Fixes\n\n## Understanding Boundary Conditions\n\nBoundary conditions are edge cases at the \"boundaries\" of input ranges that often cause bugs.\n\n## Common Boundary Issues\n\n### 1. Array Bounds Errors\n\n\\`\\`\\`javascript\n// ❌ Off-by-one error\nfor (let i = 0; i <= arr.length; i++) {\n  console.log(arr[i]); // undefined on last iteration\n}\n\n// ✅ Fixed\nfor (let i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {\n  console.log(arr[i]);\n}\n\n// ✅ Better: Use array methods\narr.forEach(item => console.log(item));\n\n// ❌ Accessing non-existent index\nfunction getFirstItem(arr) {\n  return arr[0].name; // Crashes on empty array\n}\n\n// ✅ Fixed with null check\nfunction getFirstItem(arr) {\n  return arr[0]?.name ?? null;\n}\n\n// ✅ Better: Explicit handling\nfunction getFirstItem(arr) {\n  if (arr.length === 0) {\n    throw new Error('Array is empty');\n  }\n  return arr[0].name;\n}\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n### 2. Empty/Null Input Handling\n\n\\`\\`\\`javascript\n// ❌ No null check\nfunction calculateTotal(items) {\n  return items.reduce((sum, item) => sum + item.price, 0);\n}\n\n// ✅ Fixed\nfunction calculateTotal(items) {\n  if (!items || items.length === 0) return 0;\n  return items.reduce((sum, item) => sum + (item.price ?? 0), 0);\n}\n\n// ❌ No undefined check\nfunction formatName(user) {\n  return \\`\\${user.firstName} \\${user.lastName}\\`;\n}\n\n// ✅ Fixed\nfunction formatName(u