efined errors with optional chaining, nullish coalescing, and type guards.\",\n    content: `# Null Pointer Exception Prevention Patterns\n\n## Modern JavaScript Solutions\n\n### 1. Optional Chaining (?.)\n\\`\\`\\`javascript\n// ❌ Unsafe access\nconst street = user.address.street.name;\n\n// ✅ Safe access with optional chaining\nconst street = user?.address?.street?.name;\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n### 2. Nullish Coalescing (??)\n\\`\\`\\`javascript\n// ❌ Problematic fallback\nconst name = user.name || 'Anonymous'; // Falsy values overwritten\n\n// ✅ Proper nullish coalescing\nconst name = user.name ?? 'Anonymous'; // Only null/undefined replaced\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n### 3. Combined Pattern\n\\`\\`\\`javascript\nconst config = {\n  api: {\n    endpoint: settings?.api?.endpoint ?? 'https://api.default.com',\n    timeout: settings?.api?.timeout ?? 5000,\n    retries: settings?.api?.retries ?? 3\n  }\n};\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n### 4. Array Safety\n\\`\\`\\`javascript\n// ❌ Unsafe array access\nconst firstItem = items[0].name;\n\n// ✅ Safe array access\nconst firstItem = items?.[0]?.name;\nconst firstItem = items.at(0)?.name; // Using at() method\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n### 5. Function Argument Defaults\n\\`\\`\\`javascript\n// ✅ Default parameters\nfunction greet(name = 'Guest') {\n  return \\`Hello \\${name}\\`;\n}\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n### 6. Object Destructuring with Defaults\n\\`\\`\\`javascript\n// ✅ Safe destructuring\nconst { address: { city = 'Unknown' } = {} } = user || {};\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n## React/Component Patterns\n\n\\`\\`\\`jsx\n// ✅ Safe render\nfunction UserCard({ user }) {\n  return (\n    <div>\n      <img src={user?.profile?.avatar?.url ?? '/default-avatar.png'} />\n    </div>\n  );\n}\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n## Best Practices Checklist\n\n- [ ] Use optional chaining for nested property access\n- [ ] Use nullish coalescing for default values\n- [ ] Provide default parameters for functions\n- [ ] Use type guards in TypeScript\n- [ ] Validate external data at boundaries`,\n    tags: [\"null-pointer\", \"defensive-programming\", \"javascript\", \"typescript\", \"error-prevention\"],\n    confidence: 1\n  },\n  {\n    name: \"Race Condition Detection and Fixes\",\n    summary: \"Identify and fix race conditions in async code using mutexes, proper async patterns, and atomic operations.\",\n    content: `# Race Condition Detection and Fixes\n\n## Common Race Condition Patterns\n\n### 1. Multiple Async Updates\n\\`\\`\\`javascript\n// ❌ Race condition\nlet counter = 0;\nasync function increment() {\n  const current = counter;\n  await someAsyncOperation();\n  counter = current + 1; // Lost updates!\n}\n\n// ✅ Fixed with atomic update\nlet counter = 0;\nasync function increment() {\n  await someAsyncOperation();\n  counter++; // Atomic in JS single thread\n}\n\n// ✅ Better: use functional update\nsetState(prev => prev + 1);\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n### 2. Promise Race Conditions\n\\`\\`\\`javascript\n// ❌ Multiple requests race\nlet latestData = null;\nsearchInput.addEventListener('input', async (e) => {\n  const results = await fetchResults(e.target.value);\n  latestData = results; // May overwrite newer results!\n  render(results);\n});\n\n// ✅ Fixed with abort controller\nlet abortController = null;\nsearchInput.addEventListener('input', async (e) => {\n  if (abortController) {\n    abortController.abort();\n  }\n  abortController = new AbortController();\n  \n  try {\n    const results = await fetchResults(e.target.value, {\n      signal: abortController.signal\n    });\n    render(results);\n  } catch (err) {\n    if (err.name !== 'AbortError') throw err;\n  }\n});\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n### 3. Database Race Conditions\n\\`\\`\\`javascript\n// ❌ Check-then-act pattern\nasync function transferMoney(from, to, amount) {\n  const balance = await getBalance(from);\n  if (balance < amount) throw new Error('Insufficient');\n  await deduct(from, amount);\n  await credit(to, amount); // Crash here = lost money!\n}\n\n// ✅ Fixed with transaction\nasync function transferMoney(from, to, amount) {\n  await db.transaction(async (trx) => {\n    const balance = await getBalance(from, trx);\n    if (balance < amount) throw new Error('Insufficient');\n    await deduct(from, amount, trx);\n    await credit(to, amount, trx);\n  });\n}\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n## Mutex Pattern\n\n\\`\\`\\`javascript\nclass Mutex {\n  constructor() {\n    this.queue = [];\n    this.locked = false;\n  }\n  \n  async lock() {\n    if (!this.locked) {\n      this.locked = true;\n      return;\n    }\n    await new Promise(resolve => this.queue.push(resolve));\n  }\n  \n  unlock() {\n    const next = this.queue.shift();\n    if (next) {\n      next();\n    } else {\n      this.locked = false;\n    }\n  }\n}\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n## Detection Strategies\n\n1. **Code Review**: Look for shared mutable state\n2. **Testing**: Run tests with random delays\n3. **Logging**: Add timestamps to concurrent operations\n4. **Static Analysis**: Use TypeScript + strict mode`,\n    tags: [\"race-condition\", \"async\", \"concurrency\", \"debugging\", \"javascript\"],\n    confidence: 1\n  },\n  {\n    name: \"SQL Injection Prevention Patterns\",\n    summary: \"Prevent SQL injection with parameterized queries, ORM best practices, input validation, and least privilege database access.\",\n    content: `# SQL Injection Prevention Patterns\n\n## Attack Examples\n\n\\`\\`\\`sql\n-- Input: ' OR '1'='1\nSELECT * FROM users WHERE username = '' OR '1'='1' -- Returns all users!\n\n-- Input: '; DROP TABLE users; --\nSELECT * FROM users WHERE username = ''; DROP TABLE users; --'\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n## Prevention Strategies\n\n### 1. Parameterized Queries (Primary Defense)\n\n\\`\\`\\`javascript\n// ❌ Vulnerable code\nconst query = \\`SELECT * FROM users WHERE username = '\\${username}'\\`;\nawait db.query(query);\n\n// ✅ Parameterized query (Node.js + pg)\nconst query = 'SELECT * FROM users WHERE username = $1';\nawait db.query(query, [username]);\n\n// ✅ Parameterized query (Node.js + mysql2)\nconst query = 'SELECT * FROM users WHERE username =